<TEXT>
a fire and explosion damaged a day care 
center after it opened thursday but children and staff members 
were evacuated with only minor injuries reported officials said 
framingham firefighters responding to a report of a fire at the 
kindercare learning center at 839 am thursday found the 
basement engulfed in thick black smoke said dispatcher vin schiavi 
about 30 children and 6 staff members were safely evacuated 
said deputy fire chief thomas potenza an explosion rocked the 
cellar when heat from the fire reached some aerosol cans and paint 
cans but no one was injured potenza said 
potenza said a large amount of combustible material was stacked 
in a basement storage room 
one center staff member suffered a slight laceration on the hand 
from the fire and a firefighter sustained a minor back injury 
potenza said 
damage to the center was estimated at 40000 the cellar had 
structural damage from the fire while the upper floors were 
damaged by the heavy smoke that billowed upwards potenza said 
investigators had not determined the cause of the fire thursday 
