<TEXT>
a highspeed catamaran ferry will link britain and 
france starting in june cutting the current sailing time nearly in 
half ferry operators announced 
ferry voyages between portsmouth england and cherbourg france 
now take nearly five hours 
the twinhulled christopher columbus built by international 
catamarans of tasmania will set sail for england next month and be 
ready for commercial sailings in june the ferry company 
hoverspeed said thursday 
it will carry up to 80 cars and 450 passengers travel at up to 
45 mph and cope with waves as high as 18 feet the company said 
it said other routes and the price and frequency of voyages 
will be announced later 
a giant tunnel being dug under the channel between france and 
england will offer 35minute rail crossings the 11 billion 
eurotunnel a joint project of british and french companies is 
scheduled to open in mid1993 
</TEXT>
