<TEXT>
journalists end up in deep trouble if 
they blur the line between fact and fiction but the writers at the 
american comedy network thrive on keeping people guessing about 
whats real and whats not 
take their recent spoof interview with the president when a 
george bush impersonator sought advice on finding a new enemy to 
replace the soviet union or when the presidents opinion on 
the summit at sea with mikhail gorbachev turned into a 
commentary on another superpower meeting the fight between sugar 
ray leonard and roberto duran 
since 1983 the american comedy network has been producing zany 
irreverent skits mock interviews and fake commercials that disc 
jockeys around the country use to boost the insanity level of their 
shows 
when you get up in the morning there are certain things you 
need whats the weather going to be like are the highways 
crowded said acn general manager and cofounder andy goodman 
and the other hidden ingredient is getting your day rolling and 
comedy is always good fare 
goodman and cofounder bob james were working at a radio station 
in orlando fla when newcity communications inc in bridgeport 
recruited them to produce parodies for its 11 radio stations 
five months later they hit it big with one of their mock 
commercials a parody of the atampt breakup called breakin up is 
hard on you sung to neil sedakas breakin up is hard to do 
it got so much airplay that a boston record company made it into a 
single that sold 200000 copies and broke into the top 80 on one of 
billboard magazines record charts 
within three years acn had 128 customers now it serves 274 
stations in the united states canada australia ireland new 
zealand and the us virgin islands 
acn has several competitors including rock comedy network the 
premier comedy network the country comedy network and the 
contemporary comedy network 
we started at the time when the need for comedy in radio was 
just beginning to build goodman said we were there to answer 
the call and then when everybody else jumped into the field we 
were considered the first and the best 
for 1800 to 15500 a year depending on market size radio 
stations get 10 tapes a week from acns staff of 18 plus 
freelancers 
nothing is sacred to the writers 
there was a commercial for choke cola for the denver broncos 
who have been whipped in their four super bowl appearances clients 
got a commercial for the james brown security alarm system soon 
after the godfather of souls arrest 
not everyone sees the fun in some of acns antics 
sears roebuck amp co sued over a spoof commercial for a white 
sale at fears department store in johannesburg south africa 
the nations largest retailer eventually settled for 1 in return 
for destruction of the tape 
when acn did a spot on infidelity bank it got a call from 
the chairman of the board of a fidelity bank in topeka kan who 
was afraid his customers were going to think the bank was saying 
they have sex with their customers goodman said 
some people just dont have a sense of humor goodman 
said thats one of the risks of doing something in comedy 
acn writers assemble every weekday and flip through such 
publications as people magazine usa today and the new york times 
taking the nations pulse and figuring out what will strike its 
funny bone 
their scripts wind up in the studio where acns ed kelly and 
new york comedian nancy park record most of the voices the 
finished product is dubbed onto tapes to be shipped federal express 
to acns affiliates 
the pressure to be funny week after week is enormous and four of 
the five original contributors have moved on to other careers 
goodman the last holdout also is thinking to go into television 
writing or journalism 
after seven years its hard because when you sit down to write 
your 1000th fake commercial or 500th song parody you cant say 
its as exciting as your first fake commercial goodman said 
weve done it for seven years so it just gets tough 
</TEXT>
