<TEXT>
legs are the talk of the town in milan this 
week as people try to cope with the shocking news that skirts will 
be shorter than ever next winter 
the general consensus is that toolong legs are almost as bad as 
too short but whatever the case knees must never be chubby 
this spells good news for diet experts and for workout centers 
and cosmetic companies which will undoubtedly be flooded with women 
trying to get rid of those knee dimples so cute when they were 
babies but now definitely outdated 
the most extreme version of the new fallwinter 19901991 
micromini seen at gianni versace played around the hip bone 
hardly a length for the office this came at the beginning of the 
fourday italian readytowear fashion week which closed here 
thursday 
slightly longer versions were presente by almost every designer 
showing this week with the exception of soprani ferre and armani 
who placed their hemlines a demure inch or so above the knee 
another novelty in the short hemline department is the 
introduction of sporty bermudas and short shorts into the winter 
wardrobe 
these outfits as well as the skirts are usually worn with 
ribbed wool tights or thighhigh boots 
the abbreviated hemline even creeps into fashionable night life 
with many elegant velvet and sequined gowns anything but 
floorlength 
for those who dont care for the micro look the over30 top 
italian designers showing their wares here this week revived the 
thin pencil pants in light fabric or wool jersey popular in the 
1950s 
there is a lot of sportswear in these latest collections with 
velour sweat suits knit body suits embroidered heavy knit 
sweaters and loads of fashionable parkas and duffel coats even 
jenny usually a safe address for the career woman showed lots of 
freetime outfits and afterhours hemlines 
to enoble its sporty thrust next years winter fashion uses a 
lot of gold detailing both for day and night 
the new shape is the aline which appears in dresses and 
jackets alike shoulders are narrower in general although there is 
no need to throw away your shoulder pads 
in the passamenterie department there is abundant use of silk 
cording wool braiding fringe and lace trimming 
the most used fabric of the season is velour which appears 
around the clock 
colors are either bright shades gleaned from a new england fall 
landscape or icy pastels drawn from the hues of a winter morning 
christmasbow red is the newest color although the traditional 
milan browns grays and blacks are still around they no longer 
dominate the collections 
following in alphabetical order are a few highlights from the 
shows 
armani the most graceful and feminine evening wear in delicate 
porcelain prints and beautiful embroidered velvet 
byblos cozy irish knit sweaters with gold and floral embroidery 
fendi fur down coats made out of puffed leather stuffed with 
silk 
