the first us nuclear weapons test of the year 
is scheduled for detonation saturday morning at the nevada test 
site the energy department said 
the test codenamed metropolis will be the first nuclear 
weapon exploded at the nuclear proving grounds since dec 20 
department spokesman chris west said on thursday the weapon will 
have a yield of 20 to 150 kilotons of tnt large enough for the 
agency to warn managers of highrise buildings in las vegas not to 
have workers in precarious positions at the time of the scheduled 8 
am pst detonation 
the weapon will be exploded 1500 feet beneath the surface of 
yucca flat about 85 miles north of las vegas 
last year the department of energy exploded 12 nuclear weapons 
at the sprawling desert facility where the nations nuclear 
warheads have been tested since 1951 
