all about the bored holes 
in addition inspectors at piqua allegedly approved electrical 
wires on the devices that had failed military specifications on 
solderability tests 
scarbrough said the wiring the company received was tested and 
rejected if defective and replaced by the vendor defense 
department inspectors at his plant also examined the wiring he 
said 
