nikkei index up 600 points 
but despite the morning rebound the continuing depreciation of 
the yen was worrying many investors he said 
dealers still expect the bank of japan will be forced to raise 
its discount rate to counteract the inflationary impact of the 
yens decline higher rates tend to dampen demand for stocks 
to some extent investors have discounted a possible increase 
in the discount rate but there is some uncertainty because no one 
knows whether the rise will 05 percent 10 percent ichimura 
said the rate stands at 425 percent 
the foreign exchange rate is the biggest problem it will have 
a tremendous impact on stocks he added 
