<TEXT>
a moderate earthquake measuring 55 on the 
richter scale shook wide sections of southcentral alaska early 
today but there were no immediate reports of any damage or 
injuries officials said 
the quake was centered about 60 miles northwest of homer said 
alec medbery of the alaska tsunami warning center 
it was felt all the way from kodiak island to anchorage 
palmer and seward medbery said but it was too small for a 
tsunami a sea wave generated by a quake 
the 1964 good friday alaska earthquake that measured 85 on 
the richter scale generated large waves that devastated several 
coastal communities including valdez and killed 131 people as far 
south as oregon and hawaii 
the richter scale is a measure of ground motion as recorded on 
seismographs every increase of one number means a tenfold increase 
in magnitude thus a reading of 75 reflects an earthquake 10 
times strong than one of 65 
an earthquake of magnitude 35 can cause slight damage 4 
moderate damage 5 considerable damage and 6 severe damage 
