top leaders ordered a nationwide offensive against official 
corruption last summer after watching student prodemocracy 
protesters win massive public support in large part because of 
their demands for clean government 
in recent years giftgiving has become an essential part of 
most official applications with bribes ranging from a bottle of 
liquor for a scarce ticket to cash for a passport or an apartment 
the government set up special hotlines for reporting corruption 
and offered leniency to people who confessed by years end it said 
it had received reports of more than 216000 cases and had dealt 
with more than a quarter of them 
