avoid the perils it poses for their unity 
party leader achille occhetto has the votes he needs at the 
partys extraordinary congress for the approval of his proposal to 
revamp the party a move that is expected to lead to a change of 
its name and the elimination of its hammer and sickle symbol 
but former party leader alessandro natta one of the old 
guard communists who led the campaign against creating a new 
party cautioned occhetto and his followers not to take steps that 
would split the wests largest communist party 
those who oppose the change will not estrange themselves from 
the party said natta but neither will they tolerate being put 
aside 
although occhetto controls almost 67 percent of the 1092 
delegates he still needs to negotiate with the impassioned 
minority that fought against his proposal 
occhettos proposal was sprurred by the collapse of communism in 
eastern europe and by his partys steady decline in both membership 
and electoral strength the communists nearly came to power in 1976 
when they won 34 percent of the vote but they dropped to about 27 
percent in the last parliamentary elections in 1987 
occhetto hopes a new party formation can help reverse the 
membership and electoral slides bring the party into the 
mainstream of european socialism and challenge the domination of 
the christian democrats and their allies in italy by uniting the 
countrys fractured political left 
but the entire plan could backfire if occhetto only succeeds in 
splitting his party of 14 million members his opposition has come 
from the old guard emotionally tied to ther name and symbol and 
from young members who want a more militant party one that would 
for example oppose italys membership in nato 
i have said that it would not displease me if ours remained 
the only party in the world to call itself communist natta told 
the delegates 
the fight involves political questions and the most relevant 
of these is the fate of the party a change is possible but there 
is no need to lower our flag argued natta 
we in the minority believe that the italian communist party 
has in itself the reasons the resources and the capacity for a 
renewal that will allow it to confront in this historic phase the 
demands for the struggle for democracy and for the alternative to 
the christian democrats natta said later 
while the plan to revamp the party is assured the shape of that 
new party and its name are uncertain that will be left to the 
party leadership to be elected sunday who then will present their 
proposals to another party congress for approval 
the battle lines between occhetto and his opponents at the 
congress are drawn in committee rooms where delegates are 
considering the makeup of the leadership that will draft the 
proposals for that next congress 
occhetto and his allies want to create a new executive body in 
the party to streamline the decisionmaking his opponents who 
have seen their numbers increase in the 300member central 
committee want to keep the party structures as they are 
one possible compromise would give occhetto the new executive 
body but one in which the no forces would still have a voice 
occhettos allies repeatedly have stressed to the congress they 
want to avoid any split in the party but that they understand the 
risks and want the direction of the new party to be determined by 
all the members 
we must decide to assume the responsibility of a courageous 
exceptional political initiative none of us underestimates the 
difficulties and the risks said giorgio napolitano an old guard 
communist who has supported occhetto 
in building the new party said napolitano we must do our 
work but in a free and open way we need the support of everyone 
</TEXT>
