country although it is not in israel but in the west bank 
and in the west bank settlement of ariel where 8000 people 
live about 25 miles north of jerusalem a program has been set up 
to help soviet immigrants 
it provides temporary housing free of charge and arranges for a 
family to adopt newcomers to help get them through government red 
tape language classes and assistance in finding jobs and permanent 
housing are also available 
we make them feel very wanted said dina shalit a mayoral 
assistant for immigration affairs 
