usually have family or friends among the 150 russian families who 
were among the original founders in the 1970s in the past six 
months about 55 soviet jewish families have come to ariel 
but not all the efforts are successful one reason being that 
the palestinian uprising means most settlers carry arms and have to 
be alert constantly for attackers with stones and firebombs 
leaders of the gush katif block of settlements in the gaza strip 
recently organized a tour for soviet newcomers but spokesman 
menachem beit halachmi conceded there have been no takers so far 
but the settlements have succeeded in attracting israelis 
mostly ardent nationalists who believe living on the warwon land 
will help in making it a permanent part of israel 
the settlements have grown by 15 percent in the past two years 
despite the uprising in which more than 600 palestinians and 43 
israelis have died 
most of the people who come to us are coming for ideological 
reasons despite the intefadeh harel said 
but a main attraction for many especially in the jerusalem and 
tel aviv areas is a better standard of living than can be found in 
cramped city apartments 
in the hilltop settlement of har adar six miles northwest of 
jerusalem 240 families have built luxurious carved stone villas 
for the price of a threebedroom apartment in jerusalem 
we moved out here because we wanted to live in a house and we 
couldnt afford it in the city and here we are only 20 minutes 
from downtown said debbie zuberi 33 who emigrated from san 
francisco 12 years ago and lives in a threestory home with a view 
of jerusalem 
shalit of ariel explained the trend its like the onetime 
american push to the suburbs people are looking for cleaner air 
less traffic bigger homes and better schools she said 
