their lives are linked by a common memory a cool 
vietnamese river on a steamy day gunfire then chaos each thought 
the other had died 
but this weekend in st louis 21 years later the paths of jim 
lahr and denver lawson freeman cross once again 
lahr is to receive the bronze star for pulling his wounded 
buddy freeman and another marine from the rivers green waters to 
safety lahr was shot and paralyzed from the waist down as he 
returned to the river for a third wounded man 
one of the men rescued by lahr died the captain who that day 
began the paperwork to commend lahr was wounded in another raid the 
same week 
