<TEXT>
the council of national unity voted 
friday to increase ethnic minority representation in romanias 
first freely elected parliament since 1937 while restricting the 
role of the military 
the council the makeshift parliament running the country until 
elections debated the draft electoral law governing the may 20 
elections for a 331seat twochamber parliament 
debate was at times boisterous in the vaulted neoclassical 
amphitheater where dictator nicolae ceausescus rubberstamp 
national assembly once met 
ceausescu was ousted and then executed last december in the wave 
of reforms that washed over eastern europe 
