interim president ion iliescu said friday in response to calls to 
delay any vote on the electoral law until a new constitution is 
promulgated 
the constitution is to be worked out by the new parliament 
the draft electoral law provides for the military high command 
to fill by appointment 15 seats in the new parliament in 
recognition of the militarys role in supporting the revolution 
but council members voted by a show of hands to confine the 
military seats to the weaker lower house of parliament the 
assembly of deputies and exclude them from the senate 
the draft law had provided for parliamentary representation only 
for ethnic minorities able to garner 20000 votes but the council 
voted to set aside seats for the 13 officially recognized ethnic 
groups the largest being the hungarians and germans 
