roman said his interim government will maintain the freeze on 
basic commodity prices to avoid economic dislocation but prices of 
unprocessed agricultural products should be allowed to float freely 
he said that in an effort to boost agriculture the export of 
chemical fertilizers has been halted and the government has started 
to distribute pesticides not available to farmers in the last 
years of ceausescus rule 
