tempting bryan said in a floor speech he vowed to renew his 
push for higher standards later either as a separate bill or as 
part of a package aimed at reducing the threat of global warming 
supporters described bryans move as a tactical retreat made 
necessary by last weeks cleanair deal between the senate 
leadership and the bush administration a deal to which many 
senators are committed even though they might otherwise back bryan 
the compromise deleted the fuel economy provision included in 
the bill as approved by a committee last fall 
