j anthony lukas will be broadcast sunday and tuesday essentially 
telling three separate stories of how each family is affected by 
the busing of the 1960s and 70s the children occasionally pass 
each other on the common ground of the schools 
heading one family is rachel twymon a black divorced woman with 
six children 
basically all she was after was the best education she could 
get for her children said cch pounder who plays mrs twymon 
she wasnt a spokesperson she wasnt a radical at that time 
she wasnt a member of any organization she was on welfare 
jane curtin plays alice mcgoff a widow dismayed that her seven 
children might not be allowed to attend neighborhood schools she 
joins an antibusing group eventually called powder keg 
richard thomas is colin diver an idealistic young lawyer whose 
liberal attitudes and hopes for a racially mixed society are 
challenged by reality 
the three performers never met in production because their 
stories were filmed at different times 
rachel was a very strong woman extremely forceful said 
pounder i think she ruled and not necessarily with a velvet 
glove as she tried to keep her children straight she was 
definitely the strong arm but her daughters rebelled she had a 
stricter standard for her daughters the boys got to do what they 
wanted 
the miniseries written by edward hume and directed by michael 
newell was filmed on location in toronto canada because it was 
felt the wounds had not yet healed in boston the mcgoffs and 
twymons visited the sets during filming mrs twymon died in 
january 
pounder who was born in guyana and raised mostly in england 
worked closely with a voice coach to learn the colloquial boston 
black accent 
my mother had wanted me to become a newscaster so i wouldnt 
lose my british accent she said i now reserve my british 
accent exclusively for my family 
whenever im working and doing another accent i avoid calling 
my family its hard to switch it on and off you have to be 
afflicted with a parrot tongue as my mother says 
pounder called the miniseries more than just a story of the 
busing issue 
to say that common ground is about busing in boston is to 
say that moby dick is about whaling she said lukas went off 
to document each family he got a story thats really more about 
boston itself 
pounder whose full name is carol christine hilaria pounder 
attended a roman catholic boarding school in england she went to 
college in this country when her mother who had worked at the us 
embassy in london took a job with a new york newspaper 
i started acting at the age of 9 in england she said i 
played a lot of pages i dont think i played a girl until i was 
20 it took me the longest time to say out loud that i was an 
actress it seemed to be closely linked to the oldest profession 
when i began people were skeptical and would ask oh yeah what 
have you done 
shes done plenty shes probably best known for her starring 
role in the movie bagdad cafe and a featured role in prizzis 
honor 
shes starred in two other miniseries if tomorrow comes and 
the atlanta child murders and such tv movies as murder in 
