carbide on oct 29 and 30 which helped raise the stock price 125 
cents to 22 and sold the stock a week later for a reported loss 
of 40000 gaf later sold five million carbide shares for 23 to 
salomon brothers inc 
jefferies was forced to resign from his company after pleading 
guilty to two securities law violations he named gaf as part of 
his cooperation with federal prosecutors received a suspended 
sentence and was fined 250000 last year 
