the average unemployment rate in the 12 
european community nations dipped to 86 percent in january from 
87 percent in december the ec statistics agency said friday 
henning christophersen ec commissioner for the economy said 
two very positive trends can be drawn from the recent 
unemployment statistics first unemployment is now falling or 
static in all member states and second youth unemployment is 
falling even faster 
the unemployment rate for people under 25 has fallen almost one 
percent over the last six months dropping from 172 percent to 163 
percent this compares with a more modest drop in unemployment as a 
whole from 89 to 86 percent over the same period 
unemployment was highest in ireland where 167 percent of the 
potential work force was out of work in january spain also has a 
high unemployment rate at 159 percent luxembourg with only 18 
percent of its work force out of a job had the lowest rate 
