drexel burnham lambert group inc creditors will 
receive confidential company information but no veto power over 
asset sales under a bankruptcy court agreement reached friday on 
managing liquidation of the collapsed wall street firm 
also attorneys for drexels unsecured creditors said they would 
oppose a move by the securities and exchange commission to join 
their committee drexel still owes the sec 150 million from its 
1989 settlement of securities fraud charges 
opposition to an sec role on the committee centers on 500 
million drexel already has paid the government that creditors have 
said they may seek to recover for repayment of debts 
but us bankruptcy judge howard buschman iii indicated the sec 
