a role in the case even if it was not on the creditors committe 
it is very hard to imagine a chapter 11 case disaffecting 
the single largest unsecured creditor regardless of what hat they 
wear buschman said 
under the oversight scheme approved by buschman a panel of 
three drexel board members would oversee the firms liquidation of 
about 1 billion in junk bond holdings and other assets 
a subcommittee of four creditors would attend daily meetings of 
the group receive highly confidential commercial information 
about planned transactions by 6 pm and attend a meeting the 
following morning on sales the creditors will not have veto power 
