<TEXT>
the securities and exchange commission the 
bastion of law and order on wall street is forming an advisory 
committee to help soviet bloc countries keep their infant stock 
markets orderly and honest 
but securities and soviet economic experts in this country are 
divided over whether its too soon for emerging eastern european 
economies to launch the hunt for red investor 
they want to run before they can walk said ed a hewett a 
senior fellow at the brookings institution in washington 
he and other experts on eastern european economic affairs said 
developing a banking system might be a better course of action 
